The '''Church of St. Anselm''' is a [[Roman Catholic]] [[List of churches in the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New York#Churches in Staten Island|parish church]] under the authority of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New York]], located at 151st Street at Robbins Avenue, [[Bronx, New York|Bronx]], [[New York City]]; it is in the [[Mott Haven, Bronx]] neighborhood of the [[South Bronx]]. It was established in 1891 and is staffed by the [[Augustinian Recollects]]. Previously it was staffed by the [[Benedictine Friars]]. 

==Building==
The present church was built 1918. The designs was credited to [[Gustave Steinback]] and his noted ecclesiastical architectural firm by the ''[[AIA Guide to NYC]]'' (1978) and according to Steinback's own claim to the [[American Institute of Architects]] for its registry filings.<ref name=AIA/> However, the ''[[AIA Guide to NYC]]'' (2010) has revised the architect of the design to [[Anton Kloster]].<ref name="AIANYC5.P823"/> It is possible that Kloster worked for Steinback at the time. 

